See if you're doing well washing your hands.
We all know that you have to wash them (e.g. when you come home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that to actually get rid of the germs, you have to do it the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are coming.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds to remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands.
And most of us wash them shorter.
Just warm water and ordinary soap – it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even advise them off).
By washing, we rub not only the bottoms and palms of the hand, but also: the finger tips (connected or individually) – rub them with circular movements on the inside of the other hand, the spaces between the fingers (twisting your fingers, wiping your fingers on yourself), thumbs – each thumb includes the other hand, and in such a hug we turn it a moment to the right and left.
In an emergency (when you cannot wash your hands) we should wipe hands with a wet handkerchief and then use an antibacterial gel (in the roadways, from 5 zł).
After using the public toilet, do not touch the handles or doors washed with your hands (the recommendation of the Main Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open it with a paper towel.
