The Senate has decided on key laws
The Senate adopted, without amendments, a law on the disclosure of the assets of the families of the most important civil servants and on the flights of the most important persons in the State.
52 senators voted in favour of the amendment of the Act on the property of families of civil servants, without amendments, and 14 voted against and three abstained.
The senators therefore decided to reject the 12 amendments tabled during the Wednesday debate by Senator Sławomir Rybnicki.
According to him, the amendments were intended to "civilise" the law and limit the scope of the information provided in the statement on the property situation of own children, the children of the spouse, children adapted to cases where children remain in the common household with the person obliged to make a statement.
The act on the transparency of the property of the families of the most important civil servants, the project of which was established at the office of the Prime Minister, was passed by the Sejm on 11 September.
The rules provide that, among others, the Prime Minister, ministers, Members, MEPs, Senators, Presidents: the Constitutional Court, the Supreme Administrative Court and the Supreme Court, as well as the persons at the forefront of other state institutions, will be obliged to include in the statement the personal property of the spouses, children and persons in common.
Nor did the Senate propose amendments to the Act on Flights of Key Persons in the State.
It regulates what flights are in HEAD status and who may be on board government aircraft with the most important persons in the country.
The Act also specifies who is responsible for keeping the Central Flight Register.
55 senators voted in favour of the bill without amendments, 12 opposed and four abstained.
According to the Act, each flight of the President will be a "taken on an official mission".
The President's flights will be accompanied by family members and others invited by the President.
On the other hand, only a flight "to carry out tasks directly related to the function" will be a flight on the official mission of the Prime Minister and the Sejm and Senate Marshals.
The Act also specifies the list of persons who may be accompanied by the most important persons in the country during the flight.
Members of the delegation – invited Members, Senators, representatives of the public authorities and experts – may be present on board the aircraft; persons providing technical, medical or organisational services; and journalists.
In accordance with the Act, in the event of doubts about the flights of the Sejm and Senate Marshals, the Head of the KPRM will request clarification.
If such doubts are not clarified within the time limit set, the Head of the KPRM shall be required to notify the Head of the Sejm or the Senate of the inability to organise such a flight.
