Average income per person in Poland was PLN 1693 in 2018.
In real terms (after the adjustment for the impact of price changes), it increased by 4.3% compared to 2017.
Against the back of the previous years, that's a pretty low result.
In 2016, income per person increased by 7% and a year later by 6.3%.
While income growth slows down, it also inhibits expenditure growth.
These per person amounted to PLN 1187, which means that in real terms they decreased by 0.7%.
This is the first case since 2013.
In 2017, expenditure per person increased by 1.9%, and in 2016 by 4.3%.
Household budget surveys suggest that the statistical household currently spends 70.1% of its disposable income, while in 2014 this share was still above 80%, and by 2006 it was above 90%.
